                                OOPs: Object Oriented Principles
                                    [Don't Repeat Yourself]


1. Inheritance:
    When an object acquires all the properties and behaviors of a parent object.

2. Encapsulation:
    Binding (or wrapping) code and data together into a single unit.

3. Polymorphism:
    - If one tasks is performed in different ways.
    - Overload and Override

4. Abstraction:
    - Hiding internal details and showing functionality.
    - Abstract and Interface





